+## Judgment evals (meta evals)
+
+The eval harness (`agents/evals/`) is the regression gate for prompt changes. It measures the coding
+pipeline agents against frozen gold sets so that **uplift is measured, not asserted**. Read
+[`agents/evals/README.md`](agents/evals/README.md) for the full package map, gold-set layout, and
+CLI reference.
+
+### The loop
+
+Any change to a graded prompt or a router model swap triggers a re-score:
+
+```bash
+# 1. Run a fresh scorecard and compare against the saved baseline
+meta evals compare --model coder
+
+# 2. Paste the delta output into the PR / task body so reviewers can see the
+#    per-step pass-rate changes before merging.
+```
+
+If no baseline exists yet, capture one first:
+
+```bash
+meta evals baseline --force --model coder
+```
+
+### Baseline update policy
+
+Baselines are the regression reference — **never move them casually**.
+
+- Baselines move only via `meta evals baseline --force` **after a human signs off on a verified
+  uplift** in the `compare` output.
+- If a prompt change causes a regression, revert the prompt or fix it before rebasing the baseline.
+- The baseline file lives at `agents/evals/baselines/.json` and is overwritten only with `--force`.
+
+### Holdout policy
+
+Some gold cases are marked `holdout: true` in their `case.yaml`. Holdout cases are excluded from the
+main pass-rate and tracked separately as `holdout_pass_rate`.
+
+- **Exemplars may only cite non-holdout cases.** When authoring few-shot exemplars for distillation
+  (see the [distill-evals epic](distill-fable-brief.md)), use cases that are not holdout.
+- **Holdout is what `compare` judges.** The holdout pass-rate appears in the `compare` delta table
+  and serves as the final arbiter — if the main pass-rate goes up but holdout goes down, something
+  is overfitting.
+
+### Cross-references
+
+- **Why this exists:** [`distill-fable-brief.md`](distill-fable-brief.md) — the architect brief that
+  framed the distill-evals epic (capture Fable's judgment into gold sets + tightened prompts).
+- **Package docs:** [`agents/evals/README.md`](agents/evals/README.md) — full fixture schema, step
+  keys, grader details, and CLI reference.
